#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:24
msgid ""
"SciPy consists of Python packages, called SciPy packages, that are available "
"to Python users via the ``scipy`` namespace. Each SciPy package may contain "
"other SciPy packages. And so on. Therefore, the SciPy directory tree is a "
"tree of packages with arbitrary depth and width. Any SciPy package may "
"depend on NumPy packages but the dependence on other SciPy packages should "
"be kept minimal or zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:31
msgid ""
"A SciPy package contains, in addition to its sources, the following files "
"and directories:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:34
