#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:588
msgid "Specifying config_fc options for libraries in setup.py script"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:590
msgid ""
"It is possible to specify config_fc options in setup.py scripts. For "
"example, using::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:593
msgid ""
"config.add_library('library',\n"
"                   sources=[...],\n"
"                   config_fc={'noopt':(__file__,1)})"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:597
msgid "will compile the ``library`` sources without optimization flags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:599
msgid ""
"It's recommended to specify only those config_fc options in such a way that "
"are compiler independent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:603
msgid "Getting extra Fortran 77 compiler options from source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:605
msgid ""
"Some old Fortran codes need special compiler options in order to work "
"correctly. In order to specify compiler options per source file, ``numpy."
"distutils`` Fortran compiler looks for the following pattern::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:610
msgid "CF77FLAGS(<fcompiler type>) = <fcompiler f77flags>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../DISTUTILS.rst:612
msgid ""
"in the first 20 lines of the source and use the ``f77flags`` for specified "
"type of the fcompiler (the first character ``C`` is optional)."
msgstr ""

